        <name xml:lang="en">nitric oxide</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Calculated value based on stoichiometric calculations and literature data. 
30.00614g/mol is the molar mass of nitric oxide (NO). 
92.01108g/mol is the molar mass of dinitrogen tetroxide (N2O4). 

Commercially Dinitrogen trioxide is rarely used directly, it is produced in large quantities as an intermediate in the Ostwald process.  It is here modelled as an intermediate step from the reaction of nitric oxide.</comment>
